# PlaywrightTesting.mdc
# Strong Guidance – Preferred Patterns

This document provides strong guidance for Playwright-based UI automation.
Rules are phrased as SHOULD / SHOULD NOT and represent preferred patterns for Cursor.

---

## Core Principles
- Tests SHOULD be deterministic and stable
- UI automation SHOULD validate user behavior, not business logic
- CI execution SHOULD be the primary mode
- Tests SHOULD be isolated - each test runs independently with its own storage, cookies, and data
- Tests SHOULD avoid third-party dependencies - use Network API to mock external services

---

## Preferred Stack
- TypeScript + Playwright Test
- npm + Jenkins (or GitHub Actions)
- Page Object Model (or Component Object Model)
- HTML Reporter (built-in)
- @axe-core/playwright for accessibility
- Playwright Test Agents (optional, for AI-assisted testing)

---

## Canonical Project Structure
```text
tests/ui/
 ├─ src/
 │   ├─ fixtures          # Custom fixtures (authenticated page, test data)
 │   ├─ pages             # Page Object Model classes
 │   └─ tests             # Test files (*.spec.ts)
 ├─ playwright.config.ts  # Playwright configuration
 └─ test-results/         # Test reports and traces
```

---

## Playwright Configuration (Canonical)
```typescript
import { defineConfig, devices } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  testDir: './tests/ui/src/tests',
  fullyParallel: true,
  forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI,
  retries: process.env.CI ? 2 : 0,
  workers: process.env.CI ? 1 : undefined,
  reporter: [
    ['html'],
    ['list'],
    ['junit', { outputFile: 'test-results/junit.xml' }],
  ],
  use: {
    baseURL: process.env.BASE_URL || 'http://localhost:3000',
    trace: 'on-first-retry',
    screenshot: 'only-on-failure',
    video: 'retain-on-failure',
  },
  projects: [
    {
      name: 'chromium',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Chrome'] },
    },
    {
      name: 'firefox',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Firefox'] },
    },
    {
      name: 'webkit',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Safari'] },
    },
  ],
  webServer: {
    command: 'npm run dev',
    url: 'http://localhost:3000',
    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,
  },
});
```

