## Locator Guidance

Preferred order (most resilient to least):
1. `getByRole()` - Role-based locators (button, textbox, etc.)
2. `getByLabel()` - Form labels
3. `getByPlaceholder()` - Input placeholders
4. `getByText()` - Visible text content
5. `getByTestId()` - Test IDs (data-testid attributes)
6. `locator()` with CSS selectors (fallback)
7. `locator()` with XPath (last resort)

### Locator Examples
```typescript
// Preferred: Role-based
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' }).click();

// Preferred: Label-based
await page.getByLabel('Email').fill('user@example.com');

// Acceptable: Test ID
await page.getByTestId('submit-button').click();

// Avoid: CSS selectors (unless necessary)
await page.locator('.submit-btn').click(); // Only if no better option
```

### Rules
- **SHOULD** use Playwright's built-in locators with auto-waiting
- **SHOULD** prioritize user-facing attributes over implementation details
- **SHOULD NOT** use manual waits - Playwright handles actionability automatically
- **SHOULD NOT** use CSS classes or IDs unless no better option exists

