## Actions and Assertions

### Common Actions
```typescript
// Navigation
await page.goto('/path');

// Form interactions
await page.getByLabel('Email').fill('user@example.com');
await page.getByRole('checkbox').check();
await page.getByRole('combobox').selectOption('option-value');

// Clicks and hovers
await page.getByRole('button').click();
await page.getByText('Menu').hover();

// Keyboard
await page.getByLabel('Search').press('Enter');
await page.keyboard.press('Escape');

// File uploads
await page.getByLabel('Upload').setInputFiles('path/to/file.pdf');
```

### Assertions
```typescript
// URL assertions
await expect(page).toHaveURL('/dashboard');
await expect(page).toHaveURL(/.*dashboard/);

// Visibility assertions
await expect(page.getByText('Welcome')).toBeVisible();
await expect(page.getByRole('button')).toBeEnabled();

// Text assertions
await expect(page.getByText('Success')).toContainText('Success');
await expect(page.getByRole('heading')).toHaveText('Dashboard');

// Count assertions
await expect(page.getByRole('listitem')).toHaveCount(5);

// State assertions
await expect(page.getByRole('checkbox')).toBeChecked();
```

### Rules
- **SHOULD** use Playwright's auto-waiting - no manual `waitFor` needed
- **SHOULD** use resilient assertions that handle eventual consistency
- **SHOULD NOT** use `page.waitForTimeout()` - use assertions instead
- **SHOULD NOT** mix manual waits with Playwright actions

